 If, for example, a designated person was subject to a court order resulting from a breach of a fiduciary duty imposed
by the Employee Retirement Income Security Act of 1974 (``ERISA''),

89

 or had been found to have breached a fiduciary duty as a director of a corporation, in violation of state corporation
or common law, disclosure would be required. 






