<SUMMARY>
SUMMARY:

 The EPA is proposing approval of a petition from the State of Louisiana requesting that the nonclassifiable ozone
nonattainment areas in the State be exempted from the requirement to perform the oxides of nitrogen (NO

X

) portion of the build/no-build test required by the new Federal transportation conformity rule. This petition for
exemption was submitted on August 5, 1994. 



</SUMMARY>
